overview: The user requested a thorough browser-based test of the sleep
  questionnaire application. The agent systematically navigated through the
  application, testing the questionnaire flow, form validation, report
  generation, PDF download, and admin login functionality. It also verified API
  endpoints for data submission, PDF generation, and admin data access. During
  testing, the agent confirmed that core functionalities like navigation,
  conditional fields, and form validation were working as expected. It
  identified minor issues such as ESLint warnings and an outdated page title.
  Following the testing, the agent updated the page title and committed a series
  of significant feature enhancements that were part of the application,
  including new fields for pain and chronic fatigue, enhanced mental health
  questions, a comprehensive sleep health analysis report, updated PDF
  generation, mock data for new fields, and a detailed CSV export. All changes
  were committed in logical, atomic units following conventional commit
  guidelines.
